<div type="definition">
<p>LACK JUSTICE.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general term for injustice suffered is yuān 冤 (ant. píng 平 "proper balanced treatment").</p>
<p>2. Wǎng 枉 (ant. zhí 直 "straight and lawful treatment") often refers to perversion of justice (althouth the word comes to mean "injustice suffered" by Eastern Han times).</p>
<p>3. Qǔ 曲 refers to a slightly lesser injustice one is guilty of than wǎng 枉.</p>
<p>4. Qū 屈 refers to a mild injustice suffered, milder than yuān 冤.</p>
        </div>
